The paper discusses the combination of deep neural networks with graphical models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on dense prediction problems such as stereo, optical flow, and semantic segmentation, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of truncated max-product Belief Propagation, which is a common inference method in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of backpropagation for learning, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
